\Omega \in \mathcal{C}
u_\Omega
\left\{ \begin{array}{ccccccc} \Delta u = 0,  \ in \  \Omega (\ in \ the \ weak \ sense\ ) \\ \hspace{-1.5cm}u = 1 \ in \  K \ \\ \hspace{-0.7cm}u = 0 \  on  \ \partial \Omega - K  \\ \end{array} \right. 
\mathcal{B} = \{ \Omega \in \mathcal{C} : lim \ sup_{y \rightarrow x}|\nabla u_{\Omega} (y)| \leq 1, \ \forall x \in \partial \Omega / K \}
\Omega_1 , \Omega_2 \in \mathcal{B}
\Omega_1 \cap \Omega_2 \in  \mathcal{B}. 
